<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Bards, are they the uber-class of PvP?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:33 p.m. 4/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Bards, are they the uber-class of PvP?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>In reading some of the more recent posts I got the impression that Bards may have emerged as the uber-class on the PvP server. Is this true? If so, how should Bard's be tuned so they are more on par with other classes in the 1 on 1 PvP situations?
<P>For example, how does one counter a spirited up bard who is tossing around direct damage spells that require no mana?
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
